The paper is about face recognition, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed framework involves machine learning techniques such as sparse representation and classification, which are also relevant to areas such as machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments conducted in the paper involve publicly available datasets, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and information theory (cs.IT) sub-categories.
